quran[64]{c,v,t}:
  84,1,WHEN THE sky is rent apart
  84,2,obeying her Lord in true submission
  84,3,when the earth expands
  84,4,and casts out all that is within her and becomes empty
  84,5,obeying her Lord in true submission; then
  84,6,"O man, who labour constantly to meet your Lord, shall you meet Him"
  84,7,He that is given his book in his right hand
  84,8,shall have a lenient reckoning
  84,9,and shall go back rejoicing to his people
  84,10,But he that is given his book behind his back
  84,11,shall call down destruction on himself
  84,12,and burn in the Conflagration
  84,13,for he lived rejoicing among his people
  84,14,and thought he would never turn back
  84,15,Yes; but his Lord was ever watching him
  84,16,I swear by the glow of sunset
  84,17,"by the night, and all that it envelops"
  84,18,"by the moon, in her full perfection"
  84,19,that you shall march onwards from stage to stage
  84,20,Why then do they not believe
  84,21,or kneel down in prayer when the Koran is read to them
  84,22,The unbelievers indeed are in denial
  84,23,but God knows best the falsehoods they believe in
  84,24,Therefore proclaim to them a woeful scourge
  84,25,save those who believe and do good works; for theirs is an unfailing recompense
  85,1,BY THE heaven with its constellations
  85,2,By the Promised Day
  85,3,"By the Witness, and that which is witnessed"
  85,4,Cursed¹ be the diggers of the trench
  85,5,with its consuming fire
  85,6,as they sat around it
  85,7,to witness what they did to the faithful
  85,8,"Nor did they avenge themselves on them for aught but that they believed in God, the Almighty, the Praised One"
  85,9,who has sovereignty over the heavens and the earth. And God is the Witness of all things
  85,10,"Those that persecute believers, men or women, and never repent shall have the torment of Hell, the torment of the blazing fire"
  85,11,But those that believe and do good works shall have Gardens watered by running brooks. That is the supreme triumph
  85,12,Stern indeed is the vengeance of your Lord
  85,13,He it is who brings into being and then restores to life
  85,14,Forgiving and loving
  85,15,He is the Lord of the Glorious Throne
  85,16,the Executor of His own will
  85,17,Have you not heard the story of the warriors
  85,18,of Pharaoh and of Thamūd
  85,19,Yet the unbelievers are still in denial
  85,20,God surrounds them from behind
  85,21,Surely this is a glorious Koran
  85,22,on a tablet preserved
  86,1,"BY THE heaven, and by the nightly visitant"
  86,2,Would that you knew what the nightly visitant is
  86,3,It is the star of piercing brightness
  86,4,For every soul there is a guardian
  86,5,Let man reflect from what he is created
  86,6,he was created from an ejaculated fluid
  86,7,that issues from between the loins and the ribs
  86,8,Surely He has power to bring him back
  86,9,on the day when consciences are searched
  86,10,"Helpless shall he be, with none to succour him"
  86,11,By the heaven with its recurring cycles
  86,12,"and by the earth, ever bursting with new growth"
  86,13,this¹ is a discerning utterance
  86,14,no flippant jest
  86,15,They scheme and scheme
  86,16,"and I, too, scheme and scheme"
  86,17,"Therefore bear with the unbelievers, and let them be awhile"